---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words with QU — Strategic Pattern Plays That Score Big"
  description="QU pattern words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), OPAQUE (17pts), TORQUE (15pts). Strategic QU vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble qu words, quartz scrabble points, opaque scrabble, torque scrabble word, qu pattern scrabble, qu strategy scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words with QU — Strategic Pattern Plays That Score Big","description":"QU pattern words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), OPAQUE (17pts), TORQUE (15pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-qu-strategy"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUARTZ a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! QUARTZ scores 24 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10). It combines both Q=10 and Z=10 tiles in a single word — one of the highest-scoring 6-letter words possible."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play OPAQUE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. OPAQUE scores 17 points (O=1, P=3, A=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1) as a 6-letter word. It deploys Q=10 with the required U in a common English word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TORQUE valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! TORQUE scores 15 points (T=1, O=1, R=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1). A reliable Q-deployment word using common supporting tiles that are nearly always available."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words with QU — Strategic Pattern Plays That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The Q tile is both Scrabble's greatest risk and greatest reward. At 10 points it's a scoring powerhouse, but without a U it's nearly unplayable. This guide focuses on the strongest QU-pattern words — QUARTZ at a devastating 24 points, OPAQUE at 17, and TORQUE at 15. Master these and the Q tile becomes your ally.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUARTZ (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OPAQUE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TORQUE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUASAR</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Crown Jewel</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUARTZ — 24 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10 · 6 letters · Q+Z double power tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A hard mineral found in many rocks. QUARTZ combines both Q=10 and Z=10 in a single word for 24 points from 6 tiles (4.0 pts/tile). This is one of the highest per-tile efficiencies in Scrabble. On a double-word square, that's 48 points. On triple-word: 72.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Essential QU Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 QUARTZ</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">24 pts · Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10 · Hard mineral</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪟 OPAQUE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · O=1, P=3, A=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1 · Not transparent</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚙️ TORQUE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · T=1, O=1, R=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1 · Rotational force</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎭 CLIQUE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · C=3, L=1, I=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1 · Exclusive group</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More QU Pattern Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUASAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SQUID</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUIVER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUINTET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">UNIQUE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for QU Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZ is the ultimate Q play:</span> If you hold Q and Z simultaneously, QUARTZ should be your top priority. Supporting tiles (U, A, R, T) are among the most common in the bag. Play on a premium square for devastating effect.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OPAQUE ends in -QUE pattern:</span> The -QUE ending (OPAQUE, TORQUE, CLIQUE, UNIQUE) is a powerful pattern. When you see Q+U+E on your rack, scan for words ending in QUE before trying QU- starts.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Keep U when Q might appear:</span> If Q hasn't appeared yet mid-game, keep at least one U on your rack. The Q penalty (-10 at game end) makes it worth sacrificing a point or two to hold U insurance.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">QU strategy has three tiers: <span class="text-white font-medium">QUARTZ (24pts)</span> when you also have Z, <span class="text-white font-medium">-QUE words (15-17pts)</span> like OPAQUE/TORQUE/CLIQUE for common racks, and <span class="text-white font-medium">QU- starters (15pts)</span> like QUASAR/SQUID as reliable fallbacks. Master all three tiers and Q becomes a welcome draw.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/q-words-without-u/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Q Words Without U</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/managing-the-q-tile/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Managing the Q Tile</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid QU word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
